The rise in employment dropped the unemployment rate to 5.5 per cent, from 5.7 per cent in August, near the lowest in the past four decades.Economists were anticipating just 7,500 jobs in September, with the unemployment rate unchanged. Canada’s dollar jumped after the report, rising 0.5 per cent to C$1.3227 against its U.S. counterpart at 8:33 a.m. Toronto time. Yields on government two-year bonds increased 9 basis points to 1.63 per cent. 
