As part of the proposed deal, the Canadian company is in discussions with Suzlon’s creditors to restructure the outstanding bank loans of more than 110 billion rupees (US$1.6 billion), under a so-called one-time settlement plan, the people said. Brookfield is demanding that the lenders led by State Bank of India take a haircut of as much as 50 per cent on the loans, they said. 
